---
import IdeasSidebar from "../../components/IdeasSidebar.astro";
---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>aoc — Autonomous Open Community</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="aoc defines named agent roles that co-maintain modular open source projects under explicit human accountability. Every role has a named human accountability anchor. No autonomous merges. No autonomous releases. No autonomous moderation. Provenance on every action."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/landing.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/hub-subproject.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="hub-subproject">
    <IdeasSidebar active="aoc" />

    <div class="hub-main">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hub-status-row">
          <span class="hub-chip draft">🧊 Draft</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">mosaigo meta-project</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">Agent roles · Human gates · Provenance</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">Never merges autonomously</span>
        </div>
        <h1>Autonomous Open <span class="accent">Community</span></h1>
        <p class="tagline">aoc defines named agent roles — maintainer, devrel, security-reviewer, release-manager, standards-enforcer — that co-maintain modular open source projects. Every role has a named human accountability anchor. No autonomous merges. No autonomous releases. No autonomous moderation. Provenance on every action.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="intent-callout">
          <h3>Intent</h3>
          <p>Maintainer burnout scales with project count. Triage volume, repetitive PR review, release grunt work — all grow linearly as the number of projects multiply. Agents can handle the predictable parts (event normalization, routing, triage, scanning) under explicit human gates. But the final gate stays with a named human. The merge button is the maintainer's. The publish button is the release manager's. Every agent action carries provenance: role, playbook version, human anchor, model checkpoint. This is co-maintenance, not autonomous maintenance. Agents are deputies; humans are principals.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">The idea in one picture</div>
        <h2>From forge events to human-gated action</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Every box is a step. Every arrow is a handoff. The human gate is where the principal decides, always.</p>
        <div class="pipe-diagram">forge.events ─→ event.normalize ─→ route.by.role ─┬─→ maintainer.run ─┐
                                              ├─→ devrel.run     ├─→ proposal.queue ─→ provenance.attach ─→ human.gate ─→ action.dispatch ─→ forge.write
                                              ├─→ security.run   │
                                              └─→ dependency.run ┘</div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Design principles</div>
        <h2>Six things aoc holds firm</h2>
        <div class="diff-grid">
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon primary">👤</div>
            <h3>Deputies not principals</h3>
            <p>Every role has a named human accountability anchor. The agent proposes; the human decides. Agents amplify human judgment, they don't replace it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon accent">🔒</div>
            <h3>No autonomous merges</h3>
            <p>The merge button is a human's, always. Agents can draft, comment, suggest — but the final gate is manual. Humans stay in control of what lands on main.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon success">📦</div>
            <h3>No autonomous releases</h3>
            <p>The publish button is a human's, always. Agents can collect notes, stage artifacts, run tests — but humans decide when (and whether) to ship.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon light">🛡️</div>
            <h3>No autonomous moderation against humans</h3>
            <p>Agents can flag spam, cross-post content, or auto-label issues. They never silence, ban, or delete without a human anchor reviewing and approving.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon error">📋</div>
            <h3>Provenance on every action</h3>
            <p>Every agent action logs: role name, playbook version, human anchor, model checkpoint. Auditable. Reproducible. Explainable. No shadow work.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon muted">💬</div>
            <h3>One batched comment per role per PR</h3>
            <p>No walls of bot nags. One maintainer comment. One devrel comment. One security comment. Edit, never delete. Humans read once, not N times.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Step library (target)</div>
        <h2>Normalization, routing, role playbooks, gates</h2>
        <div class="pkg-grid">
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">forge.github.events</div><div class="pkg-desc">Ingest GitHub webhooks: push, pull_request, issues, releases</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">event.normalize</div><div class="pkg-desc">Canonicalize events across forges (GitHub, GitLab, Gitea)</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">route.by.role</div><div class="pkg-desc">Dispatch normalized events to maintainer, devrel, security, release, dependency queues</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">maintainer.triage</div><div class="pkg-desc">Auto-categorize issues by template, label, priority</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">maintainer.review</div><div class="pkg-desc">Analyze PR diffs, flag breaking changes, suggest test coverage</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">devrel.draft.post</div><div class="pkg-desc">Draft release notes, announcement posts, social copy from PR metadata</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">security.cve.scan</div><div class="pkg-desc">Scan dependencies for known CVEs, surface severity and fixes</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">security.sast.diff</div><div class="pkg-desc">Run static analysis on PR diffs, flag patterns and anti-patterns</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">release.collect.notes</div><div class="pkg-desc">Aggregate commit messages, PR titles, changelog entries for a tag range</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">release.stage</div><div class="pkg-desc">Create a release draft with collected notes and auto-generated summary</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">dependency.scan</div><div class="pkg-desc">Detect dependency updates, check compatibility, flag breaking changes</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">dependency.upgrade.pr</div><div class="pkg-desc">Draft a PR for dependency upgrade with test results and changelog</div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-centered">
        <div class="section-label">The architecture</div>
        <h2>Forge events flow through Studio to role playbooks</h2>
        <div class="arch-visual">
          <div class="arch-layer accent">
            GitHub / GitLab / Gitea <span class="desc">Events: push, PR, issue, release, dependency</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">events &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer success">
            Human gate (Studio) <span class="desc">Provenance, role assignment, approval workflow</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">routes &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer light">
            Role playbooks <span class="desc">maintainer, devrel, security-reviewer, release-manager, standards-enforcer</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">audit log &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer deep">
            mosaigo <span class="desc">Engine · topics · last-value · Studio · depict audit log</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">The Five Hard Rules</div>
        <h2>Core identity of aoc</h2>
        <div class="principle-grid">
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">1</div><div><h4>Human anchor on every role</h4><p>Every agent role is bound to a named human. That human is accountable for the role's decisions. Agents amplify; humans answer.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">2</div><div><h4>No silent automation</h4><p>Every agent action is visible. Comments, PRs, label changes — all carry provenance. Humans see what agents do, why, and by whom.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">3</div><div><h4>The human gate is final</h4><p>No matter how confident the agent is, the final button press is human. Merge. Publish. Moderate. All require a human principal to decide.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">4</div><div><h4>Playbooks are live code, not black boxes</h4><p>Every step in a role's playbook is readable, versionable, auditable. Humans can inspect what the agent is doing and why.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">5</div><div><h4>No role escalation without explicit approval</h4><p>An agent role never makes decisions outside its scope. A maintainer doesn't release. A devrel doesn't merge. Scope creep is a bug.</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Roadmap</div>
        <h2>From one role to a full co-maintenance system</h2>
        <div class="principle-grid">
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">01</div><div><h4>One role one project (maintainer)</h4><p>Single maintainer role on a single test project. Event normalization. Issue triage. PR triage. One human gate. Audit log in Studio.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">02</div><div><h4>Release-manager + standards-enforcer</h4><p>Add release-manager (collect notes, stage, publish gate). Add standards-enforcer (code style, lint, format checks). Two projects.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">03</div><div><h4>Security-reviewer + dependency-tender</h4><p>Add security-reviewer (CVE scan, SAST on diffs). Add dependency role (detect updates, suggest upgrades, run compatibility tests).</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">04</div><div><h4>Devrel + storyarc integration</h4><p>Add devrel role (draft posts, release notes, announcement copy). Integrate with storyarc for templated storytelling.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">05</div><div><h4>Roadmapper + multi-project</h4><p>Add roadmapper role (aggregate issues, PRs across projects, project health dashboard). Scale to 5-10 projects.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">06</div><div><h4>Module-owner + sub-scoping</h4><p>Add module-owner role (owns a sub-project or component). Roles can delegate to other roles. Hierarchical accountability.</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-links">
          <a href="/staging/">mosaigo</a>
          <a href="/ideas/depict/">depict</a>
          <a href="/ideas/gtmd/">gtmd</a>
          <a href="/ideas/storyarc/">storyarc</a>
          <a href="/ideas/mosarch/">mosarch</a>
          <a href="/ideas/mostrade/">mostrade</a>
        </div>
        <p>Part of the <a href="/staging/">mosaigoio</a> family · 🧊 draft subproject</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
